        dc:description           "Figure 5.Collections detailsof Brachypsectracleidecostaesp.nov.at typelocality,Diamantina LakesNational Park.(A) Clumpofgidgee and bauhiniatrees where larvae were collected;(B) Base of gidgee tree showing many-layered bark flakes;(C) Two livinglarvae (3 mm and 6 mm) collected under gidgee bark flakes;(D) Newly emerged holotype femaleof B.cleidecostaesp.nov.which developed from 6 mm larva in Fig.C;(E-F) dorsal and lateral views,respectively,of silken shelter in which 6 mm larva was collected.(Photos:A-C,G.Monteith;D, G.Thompson,Queensland Museum©; E-F,F.Turco,Queensland Museum©)." ;
